data.enText: to move or turn around a central fixed point; to make sth do this

data.chText: 直升机的螺旋桨开始转动时，尽量离远点儿。
data.enText: Stay well away from the helicopter when its blades start to rotate.
if a job rotates , or if people rotate a job, they regularly change the job or regularly change who does the job

data.chText: 欧盟主席一职由其成员国轮流担任。
data.enText: The EU presidency rotates among the members.

data.chText: 我加入这个公司时，轮换过几个不同的部门。
data.enText: When I joined the company, I rotated around the different sections.

data.chText: 我们轮流值夜班，这样就不会有人总是夜班了。
data.enText: We rotate the night shift so no one has to do it all the time.

simple_means.memory_skill: rot 轮子；转 + ate 使… → 旋转

ex.chText: 火星是每24小时绕轴线自转一周吗？
ex.enText: Does Mars rotate on its axis once every 24 hours?

ex.chText: 烘烤过程中不要忘记转动托盘。
ex.enText: Don't forget to rotate the pan throughout the baking time.

synonyms.bx: 指物体围绕自己的轴或中心旋转，在特定语境中指自转。

ex.enText: Seagulls circled around above the sea.

ex.chText: 飞机在机场上空盘旋，等待指挥塔的指令。
ex.enText: The plane circled the airport, waiting for the order from the control tower.

ex.chText: 那个轮子为什么不转了？
ex.enText: Why did that wheel stop revolving?

ex.chText: 怎样才能旋转屏幕上的图像？
ex.enText: How can I revolve the image on the screen?

ex.chText: 地球绕太阳公转是常识。
ex.enText: It is common sense that the earth revolves around the sun.

synonyms.bx: 指物体像轮子一样转动，在特定语境中指公转。

ex.chText: 飞机的螺旋桨在快速旋转时，要离得远一些。
ex.enText: Stay away when the plane's propellers are spinning.

ex.chText: 那位做旋转动作的溜冰者吸引了她的注意力。
ex.enText: The spinning ice skater attracted her attention.

synonyms.bx: 强调迅速、连续地旋转，多指绕轴心转动。

ex.chText: 看！海鸥在港口上空盘旋。
ex.enText: Look! The seagulls are whirling over the harbour.

ex.chText: 新郎抱着新娘转了起来。
ex.enText: The groom whirled the bride round in his arms.

synonyms.bx: 强调速度快，含飞旋之意。

tr: plant or grow in a fixed cyclic order of succession
example: We rotate the crops so as to maximize the use of the soil

tr: perform a job or duty on a rotating basis
example: Interns have to rotate for a few months

tr: turn on or around an axis or a center
example: The Earth revolves around the Sun
The lamb roast rotates on a spit over the fire
These birds can splay out their toes
ballet dancers can rotate their legs out by 90 degrees

tr: cause to turn on an axis or center

example: We rotate the lead soprano every night

value.def: When something rotates or when you rotate it, it turns with a circular movement.

example.ex: The Earth rotates round the sun...
Take each foot in both your hands and rotate it to loosen and relax the ankle.
example.tran: 双手抓住自己的双脚，转动一下，以放松脚踝。

value.def: If people or things rotate, or if someone rotates them, they take it in turns to do a particular job or serve a particular purpose.

example.ex: The members of the club can rotate and one person can do all the preparation for the evening...
example.tran: 俱乐部的成员可以轮流工作，而且一个人就能做好晚上的所有准备工作。

example.ex: They will swap posts in a year's time, according to new party rules which rotate the leadership.
example.tran: 根据轮流担任领导的新政党章程，他们在一年后会轮换职位。

example.ex: The European Union's rotating presidency passed from Sweden to Belgium.
example.tran: 欧盟轮值主席国由瑞典换成了比利时。

partsOfSpeech.dec: rot 轮子；转 + ary …的 → 旋转的，转动的
rot 轮子；转 + ate 做，造成，使… → 旋转
rot 轮子；转 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 旋转；轮流
rot 轮子；转 + atory 场所，地点 → 旋转的；轮流的
rot 轮子；转 + or 表器物 → 旋转体
rot 轮子；转 + und → 像轮子 → 圆胖的
rotund （人）圆胖的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 圆形；圆胖
